title: Thursday's girls' soccer roundup: York Catholic bests Delone Catholic, wraps up Division III title
text:
4 
First half — 1. SW, Taylor Gough (Macy Bahlow), 21:13. 
Second half — 2. SW, Taylor Geiman (Bahlow), 37:20. 3. SW, Geiman (Abby Stevenson), 32:40. 4. SW, Bahlow, 5:44. 
Shots on goal — NO 3., SW 12. 
Corners — NO 0, SW 5. 
Goalies — NO, Brianna Ditzler (8 saves). SW, Gabby Green (3 saves). 
JV score — South Western 0, New Oxford 0. 
BIGLERVILLE 2, FAIRFIELD 2 (2OT) >> After each team scored twice in the first half, the goals disappeared as the game ended in a 2-2 draw. The draw allowed York Catholic to win Division III as the Green Knights entered action tied with the Fighting Irish. 
Biglerville's goals came from Courtney Seymore and Coral Wagner. Fairfield's Hannah Logue had a goal and an assist. Fairfield
